description: The College Savings Plans of Maryland (?CSPM?) is seeking a vendor to provide telephone answering services for calls received from current account holders in the Maryland Prepaid College Trust (?MPCT?).  The services include answering telephone calls from current account holders in the MPCT, recording details about the caller and the reason for the call, documenting certain other call details, compiling all messages received for the day, and submitting those messages daily to CSPM staff.    Daily messages are to be forwarded in Word or Adobe format to CSPM via email at the end of each business day (5:00 p.m.) but no later than 6:00 p.m. It is anticipated that the vendor will need to provide these services for approximately 3 months. Based on call volume for this time of year, the vendor can expect an average of 50 phone calls per day. Please provide a per minute quote. Contract will be awarded to the vendor whose proposal is determined to be the most advantageous to CSPM.
nigp_class_with_description: 915 - COMMUNICATIONS AND MEDIA RELATED SERVICES

short_description: ENGLISH LANGUAGE ARTS (ELA) AND MATHEMATICS ONLINE
description:
This project requires the Contractor(s) to develop 125 on-line modules that will be used for either intervention or enrichment for English Language Arts, and 125 on-line modules that will be used for either intervention or enrichment for Mathematics.  Modules shall be developed for elementary, middle, and high school.  The modules shall utilize the three UDL learning guidelines: 
?	use multiple means of representation, 
?	use multiple means of expression, and 
?	use multiple means of engagement.  
ALL COMMUNICATIONS PERTAINING TO THIS RFP SHALL BE DONE BY E-MAIL ONLY TO adelman@msde.state.md.us and refer to R00R24018147

This project requires the Contractor(s) to develop 125 on-line modules that will be used for either intervention or enrichment for English Language Arts, and 125 on-line modules that will be used for either intervention or enrichment for Mathematics.  Modules shall be developed for elementary, middle, and high school.  The modules shall utilize the three UDL learning guidelines: 
?	use multiple means of representation, 
?	use multiple means of expression, and 
?	use multiple means of engagement.  
ALL COMMUNICATIONS PERTAINING TO THIS RFP SHALL BE DONE BY E-MAIL ONLY TO adelman@msde.state.md.us and refer to R00R24018147

description: This request for a quote is to procure the services of a Consultant to develop an online application for the Maryland State Department of Education (MSDE) for the Autism Waiver Level of Care instrument.  The Level of Care instrument is the medical eligibility determination document for the Home and Community Based Services Waiver for Children with Autism Spectrum Disorder.  The Autism Waiver, through Medical Assistance, allows eligible children with Autism Spectrum Disorder to receive specific waiver services to support them in their home and community.  The LOC instrument is completed and signed by the school psychologist at the local school system and the chair of the multidisciplinary team. The online application will maintain data/information on students with Autism who have had multidisciplinary team meetings and/or a LOC completed to provide eligibility determination records/documentation for the Maryland State Department of Education (MSDE). Note:  Please refer to RFQ
nigp_class_with_description: 924 - EDUCATIONAL/TRAINING SERVICES

description: DESIGN A NEW TWO-STORY BUILDING TO PROVIDE SPACE FOR CLASSROOMS, ENGINEERING LAB, ADMINISTRATIVE & FACULTY OFFICES, MEETING SPACE, & RELATED SITE DEVELOPMENT.  MAJOR DISCIPLINES INCLUDE: ARCHITECT, CERTIFIED LEED DESIGNER, LANDSCAPE ARCHITECT, STRUCTURAL ENGINEER, CIVIL ENGINEER, GEOTECHNICAL ENGINEER, MECHANICAL ENGINEER, ELECTRICAL ENGINEER, INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY CONSULTANT, & COST CONSULTANT.  THIS IS A MULT STEP RFP PROCESS.  QUALIFICATIONS/TECHNICAL PROPOSALS WILL ONLY BE ACCEPTED FROM OFFERORS RESPONSIVE TO REQUEST FOR LETTERS OF INTEREST SOLICITATION. CONSTRUCTION BUDGET ESTIMATE
